{"id":33816,"date":"2019-11-25T10:32:14","date_gmt":"2019-11-25T06:32:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=33816"},"modified":"2025-07-08T10:48:28","modified_gmt":"2025-07-08T06:48:28","slug":"fudayl-always-recommend-mercy","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/11\/25\/fudayl-always-recommend-mercy\/","title":{"rendered":"Fudayl on Forgiveness: Always recommend mercy and forbearance"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>&#8216;Abdu Samad reported: Al-Fudayl ibn \u2018Iyad, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIf a man comes to you complaining about another man, then say: O brother, forgive him, as forgiveness is closer to righteousness. If he says my heart cannot tolerate forgiveness, but rather retaliation as Allah Almighty has commanded me, then say: If you must, do so in the best manner and retaliate with the same measure which you were afflicted, or else return to the door of forgiveness. Surely, the door of forgiveness is wider. Whoever forgives and sets things right, his reward is with Allah. The one who forgives will sleep comfortably in his bed, but the one who avenges will toss and turn over his affairs.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304&#8217; 8\/112<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e\u062f\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0641\u064f\u0636\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0636\u064d \u0631\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644 \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0627\u0643\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064c \u064a\u064e\u0634\u0652\u0643\u064f\u0648\u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0643\u064e \u0631\u064e\u